<br>
There were around 70 people there, which is a very scary thing when you are trying to squish all those people into 1 small room and have them not get near walls, etc.<br>
<br>
The groups got ported up and somehow ( whether it be lev if it works there, or people stacking at the zone in, or people sitting, or people near the walls, or... ) mobs from the other side of the zone and I think even the 2nd floor got aggroed.  Visions of Fear were running through our heads.<br>
<br>
At least 1 CLC got camped out, and several people were FD, so after the mobs picked out bones clean and walked off, the rezzing commenced and I think most if not all of the raid was rezzed in before the second wipe occured.  My claim to fame - I almost survived the second wipe!  I stood there waiting to be killed ( it was that or gate out, which I was -not- doing ) and finally the mobs killed the last person and all started to walk off, and then a Golem turned around,ran back and squished me into jelly.<br>
<br>
They got everyone rezzed in for the 2nd time and things started to look good.  Well, except for me.  I got a resist on a mob pretty early on and went down hard under it's fists, making me the first to die on this go-around.  From last to first, lucky me!<br>
<br>
We proceeded to clear all the mobs we needed to clear, with only a few scares.  There was one pull with 2 of the bone-dragon guys, along with a support mob that I don't remember.  Good assisting took them down.<br>
<br>
Half the raid then walked to the wall camp spot, but got attacked partway there, and I think lost at least half of the force.  It was controlled, and the bodies were dragged to camp 2 and rezzed while Farr came back and picked up the rest of us.  The second group got to the camp with little trouble and we all set up and prepared for more fun and mayhem.<br>
<br>
Camp 2 was pretty straightforward - pulls of 1 to 2 mobs, usually.  Assist, slay, assist slay, roll for loot, loot.  There was one pull of 5 ( right after I told my guild it was about time for a train - we chanters have a feeling for these things... ) which ended up wiping me again, as we had no healer in our group.  Maybe next time I'll leave the level 51-52 mobs for the 60+ chanter to Mez.<br>
<br>
I had to log to run to work right before the move to the Maestro.  I missed out on a lot of fun, it seems.  From what I gathered, the raid had Maestro and about 5 friends all at once.  AND, they handled it.  Great job.  After the rezzes, the raid decided to take down the 2 hands ( see the first sentence of my post ) for the War epic piece.  The hands went palm-up and there's one more happy Warrior on the Karana server.<br>
<br>
The loot was terrific - especially for the clerics who got multiple items.  There were some War, Pally, and Shammy items ( Gratz Aerann ), 1 Enchanter item, and a few other assorted items, not to mention the cash / gem drops.<br>
<br>
There were some assist problems that I noticed at first, but they didn't seem nearly as bad near the end of the raid.  Unfortunately, the beginning of the raid is when Assist is the most important with the number of mobs that can aggro the group.<br>
<br>
The further the raid went along, the more people were just jumping on the mobs as they were pulled to the camp instead of waiting for a call from the MA to join.  I'd even swear that the support melees even jumped on a mob or 2 before the MA attacked.  By then, it was getting a little lax because of the way we were slicing and dicing the opposition, but like anything - if you let yourself get sloppy in practice, you're going to be sloppy when you need to be sharp.<br>
<br>
Great job to everyone - leaders, puller, crowd controllers, healer, support melee, nukers, etc..  EVERYONE.  There were mistakes, but with 70 people, you're going to get what seem like a lot of mistakes.<br>
<br>
It was a pleasure to be a part of this KoCG raid, even though I had to miss the final Mini-boss battle and subsequent cash rolls because of what turned out to be a 5-minute job at work.  Grrr...<br>
<br>
Take care, all.  Get some sleep.  You deserve it. <p>Zymyool, Officer of the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Ancient Adventurers</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  on the Karana Server<br>
