<br>
- Levitate/SoE/DMF is a serious no no in Plane of Hate. My entire group had SoE on when we ported up and I'm pretty sure I got some hate from second floor because I got killed within 30 seconds of arriving. This fact was not in any of the four or five PoH guides I studied, nor did anyone I chatted with before the raid mention it. Well, now I know. Lev does work BTW, our SoE was not canceled on zone like in The Hole or Velks.<br>
<br>
- I never did get a straight answer regarding the use of SoW. Hate is an outdoor zone (SoW worked), but some people said &quot;Don't SoW&quot; so I didn't argue of course, but I didn't see any reason that it would be bad. There were a few times where I fell a bit behind when we were moving (because I had to invis a party member or something) and SoW would have been nice. Can anyone answer this question? Clearly SoW is useless when at camps, but may we SoW in Hate for when we move to new camps and such?<br>
<br>
- The Spite Golems will run at 5% health and they run rather fast and can't be chased because it will agro other stuff. They are also nearly 100% MR. I spoke to a few people and between us we had dozens of resisted Snares (maybe more than 100), and not a single successful Snare to my knowledge. When they run they will summon people across the zone. When they come back they will bring at least two friends, probably more. I have read unconfirmed reports that Wizard Lures land on them for resonable damage, and that they are SoWed and should be dispelled. Does anyone know if MR Debuffs land on them? We should test all resonable theories on the next Raid. We should also try to come up with a plan to deal with them when they get low on health.... Suggestions?<br>
<br>
- An idea I came up with half way through the raid based on my serious commitment to my usual role as Secondary Healer (I'm a Druid) - I made a macro button to target each enchanter by name and when I saw their message &quot;%T is Mezzed&quot; I would target them and throw heals if necessary. I propose we organize a few healer types in this manner, to keep the chanters alive. My heal spell will heal 2-3 bubs of life on most enchanters, so a Druid/Shammy is nearly as good as a Cleric in this role. I'd also throw a Regrowth on them and all the Necros/SKs every now and then when I was at full mana.<br>
<br>
- Farnn's idea of organizing the main four groups and then designating GLs for the rest of the groups and having the GL's organize their groups was nothing short of ingenious. That worked amazingly well, and would likely work equilly well in any situation! Talk about delegating nicely....<br>
<br>
- It seems that our numbers were to our disadvantage on the break in. I'd think that the breakin groups should pull the nearby houses a little more extensively before everyone goes up, but remember that this was my first Hate Raid. Then again, maybe it was the Levitate thing that got us all that hate on the big port up and that wipe was due to second floor agro.... <br>
<br>
Please post agreement, disagreement and discussions(remember that this was my first PoH Raid!!) Anyone else have observations and/or advice? Thanks all in advance. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=457258"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rinalthelis Wolfbrother</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ancientadventurers.org">&lt;Ancient Adventurers&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
