<br>
Aside from the obvious difficulty in movement caused by 70 people in a 10x10 area most things went pretty good, I think.  However, in my opinion, more things need to be ironed out prior to porting everyone up.<br>
<br>
I would say there are at least 5 brand new people each raid; with that in mind, the importance of assist needs to be stressed each raid as well.  <br>
<br>
Fighting on the wall needs some serious work.  Too many people are just fighting from below, causing the mob to be pushed up the wall quickly.  If a mob must be fought on the wall, it's usually best to encircle it instead of bombarding it only from the front.  The Maestro almost brought an army from the 2nd floor and that would have been disasterous.<br>
<br>
The raid channel is also very cluttered with non-raid chat and often questions about things that have already been repeated 4 or 5 times.  It would be most valuable if the channel only consisted of orders and updates about the raid.<br>
<br>
Overall, I had a very good time though and will do it again if possible.  Happy hunting in the meantime. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sotvfarrnusno>SOTVFarrnusno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Planes Raid Liason</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#8E9173>(12/31/02 2:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoH Mini Recap - 12/30/2002</span><hr size=1> Last night was a good night.  We had a rocky start, but we recovered and made it a good night.  I am proud of the way that we came together, there were a few places (like the Maestro mispull with Second Floor Aggro) that I don't see how we pulled off a victory.  A lot of the problems we had were leadership problems, because the first few times are going to be learning experiences for me, and to do so well the first time here (particularly after the PoF fiasco) was definitely  a good thing<br>
<br>
When we started off we had 67 people that came.  Wow.  When I saw the number we had I immediately called for no more walkins, but we ended up with more than was an organized group.  I quickly saw that making groups would take FAR too long for me to do, so I made up a new method on the spot.  I created the breakin groups like normal, and then just designated many people to be group leaders and they picked their own groups.  It was a process that worked quite well, and I might do this in the future as well.<br>
<br>
The breakin was where we had a rough time unfortunately.  When we first got up there we fought off the first crowd with only about 30% losses (Many times you wipe the breaking group or evac a few times to finally get past that first fight).  Unfortunately here is where I made my first bad decision of the night.  I immediately called for wizards to bring up the rest of the people, rather than clearing the immediate area first.  Some people had SoE on, and aggroed stuff from across the zone or second floor.  We actually didn't have too many mobs, only about 6-7 but people weren't assisting so enchanters started going down, and after that everyone died except for Q-Man, who managed to get out.  When he got back in, he rezzed our resident clickstick, and we got about half the people up before somehow we got aggro from a golem.  I don't know how we got aggro there because I didn't see anyone doing anything wrong, so it just may have been a wanderer and happened to come in aggro radius.  So we started fighting and at about 25% health it started running.  Now the golems are 100% magic resistant (not all types of magic, just magic itself) so when it started running at that high of a health bad things were going to happen.  It summoned a few people as we had clerics camp, and then came back with another golem and a cleric, and we just didn't have the firepower rezzed yet to do anything about it.  <br>
<br>
After this, things started going more smoothly.  We got that series of rezzes done without incident, and started buffing up and regening mana as best we could without sitting.  After we are ready we have our monk start pulling and he starts doing his thing.  We were able to pull consistently 1 or 2 at a time until we felt the area was clean.  The only incident during this was when another golem got away at 4% health, and summoned three people to the second floor ramp before one of them was able to finish the golem off.<br>
<br>
At this point we started to move.  I took the first 5 groups and starting going the long route over the wall to the SW camp.  Unfortunately someone was sitting too low on the wall and aggroed one of the houses on us (and over enough of a bulk of us that we had to stand and fight).  We lost about half of the people that came with that group on that fight, but we did manage to win it.  After that we were able to drag corpses to camp and start rezzing while I grabbed the others.  The other half of the raid went to camp with no incidents, which is always a good thing.  Finally at camp our monk puller went LD, never to be seen again.  So we had our Shadow Knight start pulling for us.  I want to make a note about our Shadow Knight, he had never been to this zone before, and did one of the best jobs of pulling up here that I have ever seen.<br>
<br>
We managed to clear a good portion of the zone, but it was starting to get late, and I decided to go after Maestro for an ending to the night.  Unfortunately having only been in that building twice before, and neither of those times leading a bunch of people, I made a wrong turn to end all wrong turns.  We turned one turn too late and ended up aggroing a house by itself in the NW corner on us, around 8 mobs.  Tough don't you think?  Well so did we until we found out that we had also aggroed Maestro and some of his buddies too.  All in all at one point we had Maestro and 12 mobs in camp, with no preperation whatsoever.  You say wipe right?  Somehow (I am still trying to figure out how) we managed to kill all of those mobs, and also a second floor aggro Thought Defiler without wipe.  Albiet about 3/4 of our raid force went down, but the fact that we pulled it off is nothing short of amazing.  Awesome Job guys!  Then once rezzes and buffing had been redone we went the right way to get into Maestro's house, and we killed a few annoyances that were left around that area.  We then pulled Maestro's hand, and proceeded to definger it nicely.  <br>
<br>
